GEMINI-CURSES(1)           User Commands           GEMINI-CURSES(1)

NAME
    gemini-curses - ncurses terminal interface for the Gemini API

SYNOPSIS
    gemini-curses
    gemini-curses <session_name>
    gemini-curses --resume <session_name>
    gemini-curses --list
    gemini-curses --models
    gemini-curses --test-model <model_id>
    gemini-curses --version
    gemini-curses --help

DESCRIPTION
    gemini-curses is a Python ncurses interface for Gemini. It is the
    full-screen terminal interface companion to the Bash gemini-cli tool.

    It provides:
        - scrollable transcript area
        - multiline input box
        - wrapped input display
        - mousewheel scrolling
        - mouse-assisted input cursor placement
        - named and resumable sessions
        - session rename support
        - session file browser
        - timestamped logs
        - rolling conversation context
        - memory snapshot storage in session logs
        - view/edit current memory
        - attachment extraction for code blocks
        - local file attachment support
        - generated inlineData attachment saving
        - in-app model selection
        - user-operated model testing
        - in-app API key management
        - options menu for config values
        - external editor support
        - credits/about screen

USAGE
    First-time setup from inside the interface:

        gemini-curses
            Press F3 to paste an API key.
            Press F2 to choose and test a model.

    Start a normal timestamped chat:

        gemini-curses

    Start a named full-screen chat:

        gemini-curses android-backup

    Resume a named chat:

        gemini-curses --resume android-backup

    List saved chats:

        gemini-curses --list

    List currently available Gemini models:

        gemini-curses --models

    Test one model from the shell:

        gemini-curses --test-model gemini-2.5-flash

SESSION MANAGEMENT
    gemini-curses
        Start a new timestamped session.

    gemini-curses <name>
        Start or open a named session.

    gemini-curses --resume <name>
        Resume an existing named session. If the session does not exist,
        the command exits with an error.

    gemini-curses --list
        List saved sessions.

    F4
        Open the in-app session browser. The session browser can open an
        existing session, start a new timestamped session, or rename the
        current session.

CONTROLS
    F1
        Show help.

    Enter
        Insert newline in the input box.

    Ctrl+G
        Send the current message.

    F2
        Open the model selector. The selector retrieves the model list from
        the Gemini models endpoint.

        Inside the selector:
            Enter      Activate selected model
            t          Test selected model
            s          Save selected model to config
            i          View model metadata
            q/Esc      Cancel

    F3
        Open API-key manager.

        API-key actions:
            - paste key for current session only
            - paste key and save to config
            - forget runtime key
            - remove GEMINI_API_KEY from config

    F4
        Open session browser.

    F5
        Open options menu.

    F6
        Open memory menu.

    F7
        Open file/attachment menu.

    F8
        Edit current prompt in external editor.

    F9
        Show credits/about screen.

    F10
    Ctrl+Q
        Quit the interface.

    PgUp
        Scroll transcript upward.

    PgDn
        Scroll transcript downward.

    Arrow keys
        Move cursor inside the input box or navigate selectors.

    Home
    End
        Move cursor to beginning or end of current input line.

    Ctrl+U
        Clear current input.

    Ctrl+L
        Redraw screen.

    Tab
        Insert four spaces.

MOUSE SUPPORT
    Mouse support depends on terminal emulator support for ncurses mouse
    events.

    Main chat view:

        Mouse wheel up
            Scroll transcript upward toward older output.

        Mouse wheel down
            Scroll transcript downward toward newer output.

        Left click in input area
            Place the input cursor near the clicked position.

    Lists and selectors:

        Mouse wheel up/down
            Move through visible rows.

        Left click row
            Highlight or select the clicked row.

        Double click row
            Activate the clicked row where supported.

MODEL DISCOVERY
    Available Gemini models can be listed from the command line:

        gemini-curses --models

    They can also be listed directly with curl:

        curl "https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta/models?key=YOUR_API_KEY"

    Inside the ncurses interface, press F2 to open the model selector.

MODEL TESTING
    Autoscan has been removed.

    Instead of probing every model until one works, gemini-curses now uses a
    user-operated model tester.

    In the model selector:

        t
            Test the selected model with MODEL_TEST_PROMPT and display the
            raw response.

    From the shell:

        gemini-curses --test-model <model_id>

    The tester sends one request to the selected model. The user reads the
    response and decides whether to activate or save the model.

CONFIGURATION
    Configuration file:

        ~/.config/gemini-cli/config

    The ncurses version intentionally uses the same configuration file as
    the Bash version.

    Supported keys:

        MODEL
            Gemini model identifier.

            If MODEL is not configured, gemini-curses labels
            gemini-2.5-flash as a fallback model. This is not a promise that
            the fallback is best or permanently available.

        CONTEXT_TURNS
            Number of recent user/assistant exchanges sent back to Gemini as
            conversation context.

            Default: 12

        HISTORY_LIMIT
            Legacy alias for CONTEXT_TURNS. Kept for compatibility with older
            config files.

        GEMINI_API_KEY
            Optional API key. Environment variable takes priority.

        SESSION_DIR
            Directory used for session log storage.
            Default: ~/.gpt

        ATTACHMENT_DIR
            Directory used for extracted code artifacts and generated inline
            attachments.
            Default: SESSION_DIR/attachments

        EDITOR
            External editor command used by F8 and memory editing.

            If unset, gemini-curses uses VISUAL, then EDITOR, then common
            editor fallbacks where available.

        MODEL_TEST_PROMPT
            Prompt sent by the model tester.

        MAX_ATTACHMENT_BYTES
            Maximum local file size allowed for prompt attachments.

ENVIRONMENT
    GEMINI_API_KEY
        Preferred API key source.

        Precedence:
            1. Environment variable
            2. Config file
            3. F3 runtime API-key input

    VISUAL
    EDITOR
        Used for external editor support if EDITOR is not set in config.

API KEY STORAGE
    API keys are not saved by default when pasted with F3.

    Saving the API key to config is optional and must be selected explicitly.
    Saving stores the key in plaintext.

FILES
    ~/.config/gemini-cli/config
        Configuration file.

    SESSION_DIR/*.log
        Session log files.

    ATTACHMENT_DIR/
        Extracted code block attachments, generated inlineData attachments,
        and other saved artifacts.

ATTACHMENT SYSTEM
    Code blocks returned by Gemini are extracted from terminal display and
    saved into ATTACHMENT_DIR.

    The original raw Gemini response remains preserved in the session log.

    Local files can be attached to the next prompt through F7.

    Text-like files are included as text parts. Binary/media files are sent as
    Gemini REST inlineData parts when possible.

    Generated inlineData parts returned by Gemini are saved into ATTACHMENT_DIR
    and represented in the transcript by attachment notices.

MEMORY MODEL
    gemini-curses keeps a rolling conversation context in memory.

    CONTEXT_TURNS controls how many recent user/assistant exchanges are sent
    back to Gemini with each request.

    Memory snapshots are written into the session log as system entries.
    When resuming an existing session, gemini-curses prefers the latest memory
    snapshot and falls back to rebuilding context from recent chat entries.

    F6 opens the memory menu. The memory menu can view, edit, clear, or rebuild
    current memory.

EXTERNAL EDITOR
    F8 opens the current prompt in an external editor.

    The editor is chosen in this order:
        1. EDITOR config key
        2. VISUAL environment variable
        3. EDITOR environment variable
        4. nano or vi if found

CREDITS
    F9 opens the credits/about screen.

LIMITATIONS
    - Requires Python 3 with curses support
    - Requires internet access
    - API quota restrictions apply
    - Model testing verifies only the single selected model
    - Model testing does not guarantee overall model quality
    - Mouse support depends on terminal emulator support for ncurses mouse events
    - Terminal text selection and copy behavior remain terminal-emulator features
    - Drag selection is not implemented by gemini-curses
    - Local media attachment support depends on Gemini model/API support
    - Generated image/video support depends on response parts returned by the model

